This paper deals with privacy-related information hiding and disclosure properties, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and logic (cs.LO) sub-categories. The paper also uses epistemic logic, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses theoretical case studies, which may fall under the data structures (cs.DS) or software engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories.
